deck_description: less so "destined for basedness" and more so "destined to lose 6 matches 0-2 during the may 2021 chalislime monthly" but still this past weekend i learned alot of things. that destiny board, to most people, is one of the slickest alternative win conditions and will earn you heaps of respect. that agonizing over making your deck exactly 40 cards isn't the best idea when you're already worried about not being able to include cards that would mesh great with the deck. that the edopro shuffler is a cruel god that refuses to let me see a single super poly or waking the dragon from my side deck. but most importantly, i learned that it doesn't matter if you make the greatest destiny board list in the history of yugioh, any deck that can use effects better than, or equal to, a single raigeki break, will fuck you up. my dreadful failure aside, it's plain to see how this deck can fuck. dark necrofear setting up for curse necrofear and the dark spirits keeping them in rotation, tour guide and fiendish rhino warrior to set up the grave and help go into the knightmares and maybe even accesscode, dark sanctuary keeping away attacks and protecting your spirit messages as well as giving material for linkuriboh and anima, dark spirit's mastery allowing you to go massively plus if your destiny board is destroyed halfway or your hand spells out "THE" aswell as searching a board or level 8 fiend, which includes abominable unchained soul to let you clap back if your opponent tries to remove your board. it's the coolest shit ever. and don't even get me started on the side deck, all you need to worry about is the triple super poly, waking, and mystic mine accompanied by the risky set rotation, based one day of peace, handtrap killer called by, and the goober out there you can go and yoink your opponent's most important cards, at worst getting either free material for accesscode or a free discard for super poly and dark spirit's mastery. now, i know the deck is still very flawed,   so yea, that's the deck, a whopping last place finish at the only tournament i bother joining, now leave me alone while i cry about how this somehow did worse than deck_excerpt: Another form of Cyberdark! This time we’re talking a combo deck!
deck_description:
The main combo starts with a single way of opening scrap recycler, you got 12 cards that can achieve this.

Normal summon recycler

Recycler effect mill rosenix

rosenix effect summon a token

limk for scrap wyvern

summon recycler and destroy it with wyvern

Wyvern again to summon scrap golem and destroy wyvern

use golem to summon recycler to your field

use recycler to mill cyber dragon core

use core’s effect to search Cyberdark world

link golem and recycler for protector welp

protector welp mills dragon buster

activate Cyberdark world and search a horn, edge, or keel

Use Cyberdark worlds effect to normal summon the monster you just added and then use that monster to equip dragon buster from the graveyard.

one card and you got a buster lock, this lock is fragile but if you have extenders and do a couple modifications to the combo you can get a power bound Cyberdarkness dragon with dragon buster equipped. If you’re lucky enough you can also have Cyberdark invasion set to recycle your lock when Cyberdarkness uses it’s negate, I’ve once had Cyberdarkness with buster lock, invasion, and inferno (which protects it) basically making a win game situation unless the have a kaiju, they didn’t btw and I won two turns after it was all set up.

The dots never go out? In Disney's punk "Cruella" we meet a sympathetic version of the supervillain Cruella de Vil - but the result is unfortunately not completely spotless. https://centervagt.wildapricot.org/10575712 Whether it's the adorable cartoon versions or the more realistic variations, the Dalmatians Pongo, Perdita, and their 101 puppies are for most of us a part of our childhood. In the children's films, the cute puppies are nastyly stolen by the unpleasant diva Cruella - a dramatic lady in black and white hair, who can, uh, walk over corpses to get her claws in her long-awaited fur. https://retfaerdighedens-ryttere.wildapricot.org/news/10575834 In the 2021 "Cruella", we start again from the beginning and meet a young Estella (Emma Stone), miles from the terrifying Cruella we feel today. Estella has hopes and dreams of becoming a fashion designer, but life takes its toll and in a tragic accident involving her own mother, both fear and disgust for Dalmatian dogs arise. As a troubled teenager, she ends up on the streets among London's shady neighborhoods. https://wptest.candle.com.tw/community/profile/conanfilm2021/ Together with newcomer companions Jasper (Joel Fry) and Horace (Paul Water Hauser), the petty thieves make the streets unsafe - until Estella encounters the biggest boss of them all, the Baroness (Emma Thompson). Estella now has to weigh how much of herself is the everyday and friendly Estella, and how much is now taken up by her more theatrical persona - Cruella. https://oldpelicula2021.wildapricot.org/pelicula/10576619 In the footsteps of the acclaimed "Joker" (2019), "Birds of Prey" (2020), and the upcoming TV series "Loki" (2021), it is thus villain stories that are highly topical on the wallpaper.  https://pakleneulice9.wildapricot.org/ Nobody wants to see a hell hero save the cat from the tree, we rather want to see how the torn cat ended up there from the very beginning. "Cruella" wants to be challenging and extravagant, but the film comes to itself that it is ultimately part of a family-oriented Disney world. Cruella is a difficult figure to deal with, you have to give it to them anyway. A lot of other famous villains, for example Cinderella's "Maleficent" (2014) gave us a anything but light-hearted background story that made the fairy tales' division into black or white blurred at the edges. But Cruella, how do you instill sympathy in such a hated character - the one who literally made fur coats out of dogs? The soundtrack to "Cruella" is awesome with The Clash, Blondie, and The Doors. There are cool costumes, glamorous balls, and the vicious fashion and clothing-filled scenes of the dynamics of "The Devil Wears Prada" (2006). But with a superficial theme, unfortunately, also comes a superficial result, as the desire to get a time-typical depth in Emma Stone's villain is spun away in the eagerness to make the film both dramatic and furiously elegant. https://steemit.com/denmark/@dk-sv-no-fi/synopsis-cruella-og-hvordan-man-ser-online-med-tekst-dansk "Cruella" is definitely a cool film, where both Emma Thompson and Emma Stone make spotless contributions as their respective fashion stars. As the film is supposed to be edgy and a relatively dark story, I strongly miss the humorous touch that Glenn Close added in his role as live-action Cruella in "101 Dalmatians" (1996). The rest of the film is too long, too annoying - all the gala events will soon be tiring to watch - and not as innovative as I had imagined. "Cruella" does not deserve all the barking, but it would clearly have offered more nostalgia and less superficiality.

deck_excerpt: A fun deck built around Doom Shaman, a gemini monster that special summons fiends from the GY!
deck_description: A fun deck built around Doom Shaman, a gemini monster that special summons fiends from the GY!  Since geminis are the most forgotten monster type in Yugioh, this is a for-fun deck. The deck is built using the March 2021 banlist. Level-8 fiends provide attack power and removal to the deck, while Chaos Hunter or Barrier Statue of the Abyss can lock the opponent down and Card Guard can protect Doom Shaman. Dark Grepher sends the fiend you need to the GY and Relinkuriboh provides some utility. Catalyst Field and the squire engine to normal summon Doom Shaman, Dark Magic Veil to revive Doom Shaman, Sinsiter Yorishiro protects your fiends, and the rest is Pot of Prosperity for consistency and power cards from the limited list.

deck_description: In this Deck you want to get the Independent Nightingale out and tribut him to Summon The Tyrant Neptun, which than has 6000ATK, 5000 Burn Damage and on that he is Unaffected by other cards. You first get out 3 Madolche Monsters, which is really easy. You only need Madolche Pettingcessour (Special Summon) or Madolche Salon (2 Normal Summons) and then Anjelly or Magilene. Then you can get out up to 4 Madolche Monsters. Then XYZ them to King of the Ferral Imps and you search out Tyrant Neptun. You Link King of the Ferral Imps or a Madolche Monster and one other Madolche Monster for Verte Anaconda. You use his effect to copy Instant fusion from the Deck and then Special summon Independent Nightingale. Tribute him to Summon Neptun and BOOM. One big Boss Monster. Tyrant Neptun (Banned) and Instant Fusion (Limited) are the only cards that are on the Bannlist.

deck_excerpt: Summon Megalith to summon more Megalith, Impcantation to reach an return more Megalith.
deck_description: Gonna say this at the start, YOU DON'T HAVE TO HAVE AN EXTRA DECK, this deck can still run just fine in fun casual games without an extra deck or you can add your own cards to the extra deck whatever. The monster you will be using to kill you opponent will be Megalith Phaleg because of it's attack boost for each ritual card  in your GY, this also works best when this is two or more of Phaleg on the flied as the attack boost stacks and you use a lot of ritual card to summon ritual card. Megalith Bethor popping effect is also great because you should at least have two different ritual cards in your GY by the time you summon Bethor. Megalith Phul is the best way to summon Megalith monsters, since you can target cards in your deck and then ditch cards from your hand putting them into the GY. But since it is also a quick effect if you can activate during your opponents turn to summon something like Megalith Bethor to destroy their card during their turn. The Impcantation cards are there for search and return, Impcantation Talismandra on summon from deck adds Megalith ritual monster, Impcantation Penciplume returns Megalith ritual monster from GY, though Talismandra and Penciplume you can reveal ritual and summon the other from deck you can use Impcantation Chalislime to discard it's self to summon one from deck. Impcantations are also useful for some ritual summon even Megalith ritual summons. Megalith Emergence and Megalith Promotion sometimes feel too slow with the deck I like them out them even though Megalith Emergence is a life saver sometimes. Barrier Statue of the Drought is something you can add because you don't normal summons monster. Remember you don't need any extra deck. Also I checked and sadly Pre-Preparation of Rites can't target Impcantation Inception

This is Quattro's Gimmick Puppets deck, so I made it from myself to see how good. 

Some cards would discard and banish effects. So I got some spell or trap cards that would bring cards that were banished, back to the graveyard and bring cards back to your deck. Also, some cards would destroy your opponent's cards and special summoned from your graveyard

So give it a try playing this deck.

This deck is based around the OCG set Vol.1 (Known as the Dark Magician Pack in the Eternal Duelist Soul Game).  No banlist, nor  Expert Rules were released yet; you could Normal Summon or Set without Tributes then.

deck_excerpt: @Ignisters bringing the Cyberse Power back from the dead.
deck_description: First debuted in the 2020 IGNITION ASSAULT, the @Ignister archetype is one of the many other Cyberse archetypes around the game, alongside with Salamangreats, Mathmechs, and Marincess. This deck in its own way has gained even more consistency with the new cards that came in the latest Booster Pack, LIGHTNING OVERDRIVE. With the addition of cards like "A.I. Meet You", and the newest Link-1 monster for the archetype, "Dark Infant @Ignister", which added the more consistency to the Deck. The main strategy of the Deck is swarming your Cyberse monsters, from your hand, Graveyard, and Extra Deck, which can be easily made with their field Spell "Ignister A.I. Land", that allows you to Special Summon your Ignister monsters from your hand, as long as you control no monsters in your Main Monster Zone, and you can use its effect as many times you can! Since this card is a Once Per-Attribute, which makes you not able to Special Summon a second monster with the same Attribute as another @Ignister you summoned previously with its effect. To Special Summon your @Ignister monsters from your graveyard you can use cards like "A.I.Dle Reborn", which is a Quick-Play Spell that lets you Summon any of your @Ignisters, "Splash Mage" for a single multi reborn, and "Transcode Talker" for your Link Monsters, which can be used for a Link Summon of "Accesscode Talker" that can bring you the win in many cases. For more disruptions you can run basic trap cards, such as "Infinite Impermanence", "Paleozoic Dinomischus", "Solemn Strike", and in optional, "Compulsory Evacuation Device". Simple Combo: This combo is a simple one, which all you need is 1 Achichi, and 1 Doyon in your hand. You first Normal Summon your Achichi, and you search for a Bururu @Ignister. Next you are going to Link Summon into your Dark Infant, which will let you add an Ignister A.I. Land directly from your Deck. Activating your A.I. Land you are going to use its effect to Special Summon Bururu, and using Bururu's effect to Send a Pikari @Ignister from your Deck to your Graveyard. Using your Dark Infant and your Bururu, you go for a Link-2 of Splash Mage. Following that you use your Ignister A.I. Land to Special Summon your Doyon, and using its effect to add Pikari from your Graveyard to your hand. Using Splash Mage's effect you can either Summon your Bururu or Achichi, which doesn't matter which you want to Summon. By Linking your 3 monsters, Doyon, Splash Mage, and your Special Summoned monster into a Link Summon of Dark Templar @Ignister. Ignister A.I. Land to a Special Summon of your Pikari, triggering your Dark Templar, which in this card you are going to declare Pikari's effect before the Dark Templar. With Dark Templar, you are going to Summon your Bururu, and Doyon, and with Pikari you are going to add A.I.Dle Reborn to your hand. Next you Synchro Summon using your Bururu and Doyon into Wind Pegasus @Ignister  triggering Bururu's effect, while allows you to Summon 1 of the Synchro Materials used for the Synchro Summon, bringing back Doyon. Using Pikari's second effect, you are going to make your Wind Pegasus a Level 4, and using Pikari and Wind Pegasus for an Xyz Summon of Light Dragon @Ignister . And finally, using your Doyon and Dark Templar into your Link-4 Topologic Bomber Dragon , and ending by setting your A.I.Dle Reborn. This combo gives you a monster destruction by using Topologic Bomber's effect and A.I.Dle Reborn to Special Summon any of your @Ignisters, and combining Light Dragon's effect that prevents destruction in order to protect your monsters. And when using Light Dragon's effect that protects your monsters, you must detach Wind Pegasus in order to use its effect in the Graveyard when you are able. Final Analysis: Deck Strengths 👍: Searching: 5/5 Swarm: 5/5 Attack: 4.5/5 Versatility: 4/5 Defense: 3/5 OTK: 4/5 Control: 3/5 Comeback: 3/5 Deck Weaknesses 👎: Graveyard Restrictions (Necrovalley, Dimensional Shifter...): 5/5 Special Summon Restrictions (TCBO, Summon Limit...): 4/5 Extra Deck Restrictions (Monarchs, Vanity's Fiend...): 4/5 Hand Traps (Nibiru, Ash Blossom, Ghost Ogre...): 4/5 Tribute to your Field monsters (Kaijus, Sphere Mode...) 4/5 Field Destruction (Raigeki, Lightning Storm): 3/5 Spell/Trap Removal (Cosmic Cyclone, Mystic Space Typhoon...): 2/5 Beat Stick monsters (ATK 3000 or higher): 1/5
Gain LP and stay around a long time~

Orcust is a mid-range strategy which focus lies on getting orcust monsters into the gy, so they can banish themself and get some advantage.  2019 Orcust was the strongest deck of the TOSS/Eternal Format, it was generic (until the mermaid ban), it could make VFD (until the rusty ban), had an very good grindgame and had cards like crescendo and dingirsu which were pretty good interuptions and protections. And then the 2020 banlist happened and pretty much killed the deck with the ban of harp horror, many orcust players hoped that mekk-knight orcust girsu could make the deck good again, but sadly it failed and MR5 wasn't helping. With the new Eldlich deck which was combined with the jet-synchro/halqifibrax/auroradon combo and adamanicipator which could gain huge amounts of advantage with block dragon and make almost unbreakable boards with a buster dragon lock, the age of orcust was over.  Until some crazy dude thought: Wait a sec... Eldlich has a pretty good grind game, wasn't there another good grind deck which was meta and had pretty good cards. And this is probably how Orcust Eldlich was created, sadly this deck toped 2 times (as much as I know) and harp is still banned. So the deck is not a tier 1 contender, but hey the deck looks like a good rogue/tier 2 deck to me.   So basically the deck uses the orcust engine to get crescendo, which is an omni negate as a counter trap. And they also use it to get dingirsu which protects your backrow from stuff like lightning storm, sends a card on the field to the gy and recycles banished orcust monster. The other engine is eldlich which replaces traps, can summon golden lord as a beatstick with protection and uses golden lord as interuption. The rest is just stuff like solemns, torrential or droplet.  You could also play pot of disparity, but I personally like the non-disparity version more. In the end there is just 1 thing to say: BRING HARP BACK TO 1 KONAMI!!!

deck_excerpt: Eldlich and lair of darkness - who'd have thought.
deck_description:
With just one tour guide in hand you can go into a herald of the arc light and Borreload savage dragon by using Auroradon, deskbot 001, Coltwing and Dark resonator.

Auroradon is prefect for a lair of darkness deck as you will come to see if you play this deck.

You can use a cursed eldland to bate an ash and then follow through with this combo.

With lair of darkness on the field, you can tribute golden lord for either of the viruses to get rid of their spell, traps or monsters with 1500 or less def.

this deck can be blocky at times but it's really fun to play if you draw a decent enough hand.

Any improvements would be appreciated.

Hope you enjoy this composition.

Stone: It's interesting, because Estella gets rejected at some point. She is cute but not completely realized. There's something exciting about Cruella, she's who she is. I'm more interested in her world. But she crosses certain boundaries that I would never do but… I prefer Cruella. it's so much fun to play over! https://hairlosshelp.dk/community/profile/centervagt/ She does not think she's the villain. deck_excerpt: Like Burning Abyss but want a way to make your opponent unable to play? This is the deck for you!
deck_description:
The full combo for this deck is opening up 2 level 3 monsters and either
feather storm or trap trick which gets us our feather storm.
Besides that you pretty much play a regular Burning Abyss.
This allows us to just simply go second, while virtually FTKing when
going first. The lock is very devasating, although counters do exist.
One can then easily side out the simorgh/feather storm engine game 2
and 3 if you are playing a match.This lock might even have competitive potential, although the pricetag
might scare some people away.
In reality many expensive cards can be replaced however.
